metadata.name: The tale of a boy
metadata.description:
"Those who don't believe in magic, will never find it" - Roald Dahl

Unlike adults, children don't read books to escape reality. They read books to make sense of it.  
If we could see the world through their eyes, we would understand that magic is real...magic exists.  
But in order to find magic around us, we must carry magic inside us.
